Package com.mathmaster13.fynotek

Class OldFynotekWord

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mathmaster13.fynotek.FynotekParent
      • com.mathmaster13.fynotek.OldFynotekWord
  • public class OldFynotekWord
extends FynotekParent
    A class for handling words in an older version of Fynotek. All objects created by this class are immutable. Old Fynotek documentation can be found here.

      • verbTense

        public OldFynotekWord verbTense​(char tenseOfVerb,
                                boolean hypothetical)
        Returns this OldFynotekWord inflected for the verb tense specified by tenseOfVerb. tenseOfVerb should be either 'p' (present), 'a' (past), 'f' (future), or 'g' (gnomic). All other charcters will cause the original object to be returned. If hypothetical is set to true, the word will be marked for a hypothetical tense; otherwise, the word will be inflected for a non-hypothetical tense. Note that verbTense('g', false) and verbTense('g', true) will always return the same result.
        Overrides:
        verbTense in class FynotekParent
        Parameters:
        tenseOfVerb - the verb tense to inflect this OldFynotekWord for.
        hypothetical - whether this word should be inflected for a hypothetical tense or not.
        Returns:
        this OldFynotekWord inflected for the specified verb tense.
        See Also:
        FynotekParent.match(FynotekParent), FynotekParent.verbTense(char, boolean)

      • isValidSequence

        public static boolean isValidSequence​(java.lang.String sequence)
        Returns whether the given sequence is phonotactically and orthographically valid in old Fynotek. Capitalization is ignored (for example, "A" and "a" are treated the same way). Multiple words can be separated by whitespace, and this function will only return true if all words in sequence are valid. Leading and trailing whitespace is ignored (the String.trim() method is called on sequence). A sequence containing punctuation marks, numbers, or other non-letter characters (with the exception of ') returns false, as well as an empty sequence or one containing only whitespace.
        Parameters:
        sequence - the sequence to be checked for validity.
        Returns:
        true if sequence is a valid sequence, and false if otherwise.
